.TH "HTMLSelectElement.value" "JS" "May 31, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLSelectElement.value \- HTMLSelectElement: value property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLSelectElement.value\f[B]\f[R] property contains the
value of the first selected \f[CR]<option>\f[R] element associated with
this \f[CR]<select>\f[R] element.
.PP
This property can also be set directly, for example to set a default
value based on some condition.
.SH VALUE
A string containing the value of the first selected \f[CR]<option>\f[R]
element in this \f[CR]<select>\f[R] element, or the empty string if no
options are selected.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Retrieving the selected value
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]label\f[R] for=\[dq]bird\-select\[dq]>Choose a bird:</\f[B]label\f[R]>

<\f[B]select\f[R] name=\[dq]birds\[dq] id=\[dq]bird\-select\[dq]>
  <\f[B]option\f[R] value=\[dq]\[dq]>\-\-Please choose an option\-\-</\f[B]option\f[R]>
  <\f[B]option\f[R] value=\[dq]Scarlet ibis\[dq]>Scarlet ibis</\f[B]option\f[R]>
  <\f[B]option\f[R] value=\[dq]Marabou stork\[dq]>Marabou stork</\f[B]option\f[R]>
  <\f[B]option\f[R] value=\[dq]Roseate spoonbill\[dq]>Roseate spoonbill</\f[B]option\f[R]>
</\f[B]select\f[R]>

<\f[B]pre\f[R] id=\[dq]log\[dq]></\f[B]pre\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] logElement = document.querySelector(\[dq]#log\[dq]);
\f[B]function\f[R] log(text) {
  logElement.innerText = text;
}

\f[B]const\f[R] select = document.querySelector(\[dq]#bird\-select\[dq]);
select.addEventListener(\[dq]change\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\[ga]Selection: ${select.value}\[ga]);
});
.EE
